member_experience_collection.title: Chief Executive Officer & Co-Founder
member_experience_collection.company_name: Struggly
member_experience_collection.description: Struggly is an online math learning program for children grades K-8 that draws upon three high impact research spaces: neuroscience, mathematics education, and growth mindset for use at school or at home. Research tells us that when we are struggling it is the best time to learn and grow--but it often times does not feel good to struggle- especially in math. Struggly is on a mission to reposition moments of struggle as exciting learning opportunities so that all students can reach their full mathematics potential. We provide students with challenging math tasks that are creative and engaging with an irresistable game-like pulll.

member_awards_collection.title: The Marjorie Lozoff Award for Research on Women and Gender
member_awards_collection.issuer: The Clayman Institute for Gender Research at Stanford University
member_awards_collection.description: This prize honors the memory of Marjorie Morse Lozoff. In an extraordinarily productive life as wife, mother, sociologist, social worker, teacher, researcher, and community leader, Marjorie Lozoff served as a model for the idea that most deeply absorbed her: furthering women's development for the benefit of women, men, children, and society. The Marjorie Lozoff Award for Research on Women and Gender is given to a graduate student conducting research on issues related to Lozoff’s interests.
